solution: ```class Solution {
    public int brokenCalc(int startValue, int target) {
        int ops = 0;
        while (target > startValue) {
            if (target % 2 == 1) {
                target++;
            } else {
                target /= 2;
            }
            ops++;
        }
        return ops + (startValue - target);
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log target)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Work backwards from target to startValue. If target is larger, halve it when even (reverse of multiply) or increment when odd (reverse of subtract). Each step roughly halves target, giving logarithmic time. Final difference adds direct subtraction steps.

